نْهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he slew the slayer of his relation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) Lebeed says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waAln~iybu A_ino taEoru min~iY rim~apF xalaqFA * \n                     \n                        baEoda AlmamaAti faA_in~iY kunotu A^av~ay^iru *"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the old she-camels, if they seek to obtain benefit from a worn rotten bone of me after death, I used to retaliate"},{"kind":"text","text":"upon them by anticipation]: (T, S:) i. e., I used to slaughter [some of] them for guests, and so I have retaliated upon them during my life for their nibbling my rotten bones"},{"kind":"page_break","n":328},{"kind":"text","text":"after my death: for when camels do not find herbage of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":", they eat the bones of dead men and of camels instead thereof. (T.) ―         -b2-  See also 1."}],"source_refs":["M","K","T","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}